<title type="html"><![CDATA[Re: Opinions on automatic code doccumentation tools ?]]></title>

<content type="html" xml:base="http://forums.nesdev.com/viewtopic.php?t=10420&amp;p=117135#p117135"><![CDATA[
I use C# and I love the code documentation. Very handy with intellisense. Compilation of the program even produces an XML file that can be distributed alongside an EXE or DLL for intellisense support. I've tried using doxygen to produce HTML documentation for C#. It really wasn't too painful.<br /><br />Typically, I'll only add code documentation for something that's not completely obvious by looking at function/parameter names and types. If I write code that I'm expecting to share, I'll go much heavier on the code documentation.<p>Statistics: Posted by <a href="http://forums.nesdev.com/memberlist.php?mode=viewprofile&amp;u=4871">snarfblam</a> — Tue Aug 27, 2013 6:23 am</p><hr />
